parse: Verb - Perfect Indicative Active - 2nd Person Plural

str2: Neuter of hostis as conjunction; demonstrative, that; causative, because.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 1st Person Plural
str2: Properly, to distinguish, i.e. Decide; by implication, to try, condemn, punish.
From aggello; a messenger; especially an 'angel'; by implication, a pastor.
Let alone, much less, much more. From meti and ge; not at all then, i.e. Not to say.
Belonging to ordinary life, worldly. From a derivative of bioo; relating to the present existence.
